{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "spring-rag-app-collection",
    "name": "Spring RAG App",
    "description": "Complete API collection for the Spring Boot RAG application.\n\nBase URL: http://localhost:8082\n\nAuthentication: JWT Bearer Token\n- Login first to get the token\n- Set the {{token}} collection variable automatically via the login request\n- All protected endpoints use {{token}} automatically\n\nUsers:\n- admin / admin123  (ROLE_ADMIN)\n- user  / user123   (ROLE_USER)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8082",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "documentId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Authentication endpoints. Login to receive a JWT token.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (admin)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.token);",
                  "    console.log('Token saved to collection variable');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"admin\",\n  \"password\": \"admin123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Login as admin (ROLE_ADMIN). The test script automatically saves the JWT token to the {{token}} collection variable."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (user)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.token);",
                  "    console.log('Token saved to collection variable');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"user\",\n  \"password\": \"user123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Login as regular user (ROLE_USER). Note: user role cannot access /actuator/** endpoints (admin only)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Documents",
      "description": "Document management endpoints. Upload documents for RAG ingestion and list uploaded documents.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Upload Document",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.documentId) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('documentId', json.documentId);",
                  "    console.log('documentId saved: ' + json.documentId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "Select a .txt, .pdf, .docx, or other Tika-supported file"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents/upload",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "documents", "upload"]
            },
            "description": "Upload a document for RAG ingestion.\n\nThe document is:\n1. Parsed by Apache Tika (supports PDF, DOCX, TXT, HTML, etc.)\n2. Split into ~800-token chunks with 100-token overlap\n3. Embedded via ONNX all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (384-dim vectors)\n4. Stored in the in-memory SimpleVectorStore\n\nThe test script saves the returned documentId to {{documentId}}."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List Documents",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "documents"]
            },
            "description": "List all uploaded documents with their metadata (documentId, filename, chunk count, upload timestamp)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Query",
      "description": "RAG query endpoints.\n\n- Per-document query: searches only within a specific document's chunks\n- Global query: searches across all uploaded documents",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Query — Per Document",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"question\": \"What is this document about?\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}/query",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "documents", "{{documentId}}", "query"]
            },
            "description": "Ask a question scoped to a single document.\n\nRAG pipeline:\n1. Embed the question (ONNX all-MiniLM-L6-v2)\n2. Similarity search filtered by documentId metadata\n3. Retrieve top-4 most relevant chunks\n4. Build system prompt with chunks as context\n5. Send to Gemini 2.5 Flash\n6. Return answer + relevant chunk excerpts\n\nReplace {{documentId}} or set it via the Upload Document request."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Query — Global (All Documents)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"question\": \"Summarise everything you know from the uploaded documents.\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/query",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "query"]
            },
            "description": "Ask a question across all uploaded documents (no documentId filter).\n\nThe response documentId will be \"ALL_DOCUMENTS\".\n\nRAG pipeline:\n1. Embed the question\n2. Cosine similarity search across ALL chunks from ALL documents\n3. Retrieve top-4 globally most relevant chunks (may span multiple documents)\n4. Build prompt and call Gemini 2.5 Flash\n5. Return answer + top chunk excerpts (first 200 chars each)"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Actuator",
      "description": "Spring Boot Actuator endpoints for monitoring and operations.\n\nAccess rules:\n- /actuator/health  — PUBLIC (no token needed)\n- /actuator/info    — PUBLIC (no token needed)\n- /actuator/**      — ADMIN only (login as admin first)\n\nExposed endpoints: health, info, metrics, env, beans, mappings, loggers",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health (public)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Application health check. Public — no token required.\n\nReturns status UP/DOWN and component-level health (diskSpace, ping).\n\nFull health details (component breakdown) are only shown when authenticated."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Info (public)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/info",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "info"]
            },
            "description": "Application info. Public — no token required.\n\nReturns app name, description, and version from application.properties (info.app.*)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Metrics — Index",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/metrics",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "metrics"]
            },
            "description": "Lists all available metric names. Requires ADMIN token.\n\nUse the metric name in GET /actuator/metrics/{metricName} to get specific values."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Metrics — JVM Memory Used",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/metrics/jvm.memory.used",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "metrics", "jvm.memory.used"]
            },
            "description": "Current JVM memory usage in bytes. Requires ADMIN token."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Metrics — HTTP Server Requests",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/metrics/http.server.requests",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "metrics", "http.server.requests"]
            },
            "description": "HTTP request count and timing statistics. Requires ADMIN token."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Environment",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/env",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "env"]
            },
            "description": "Full application environment — property sources, active profiles, system properties. Requires ADMIN token.\n\nSensitive values (passwords, secrets) are automatically masked as ******."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Beans",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/beans",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "beans"]
            },
            "description": "Lists all Spring beans registered in the application context. Requires ADMIN token.\n\nUseful for verifying that embeddingModel, vectorStore, chatModel beans are loaded correctly."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Mappings",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/mappings",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "mappings"]
            },
            "description": "Lists all @RequestMapping routes registered in the application. Requires ADMIN token.\n\nShows every endpoint: method, path, handler class."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Loggers",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/loggers",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "loggers"]
            },
            "description": "Lists all loggers and their current log levels. Requires ADMIN token.\n\nYou can also POST to /actuator/loggers/{name} to change a log level at runtime without restarting."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Loggers — Change Log Level",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"configuredLevel\": \"DEBUG\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/loggers/com.ragapp",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "loggers", "com.ragapp"]
            },
            "description": "Dynamically change the log level for com.ragapp (or any logger) at runtime. Requires ADMIN token.\n\nValid levels: TRACE, DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR, FATAL, OFF\n\nChange back to INFO with {\"configuredLevel\": \"INFO\"}"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
